/**
 * Memoizes a pure function. Args must be JSON-serializable.
 */
const memoize = (fn) => {
  const cache = new Map();

  return (...args) => {
    const key = (() => {
      try {
        return JSON.stringify(args);
      } catch (_) {
        return null;
      }
    })();

    if (key !== null && cache.has(key)) return cache.get(key);
    const result = fn(...args);
    if (key !== null) cache.set(key, result);
    return result;
  };
};
```

The `memoize` factory is pure — the cache lives entirely within the returned closure. Falls back gracefully (skips caching) if args can't be serialized. `const` throughout, no external mutations.

